moderators.label: Number of Items on Dark Triad

dokumentation.title: Prinz, G. M. (2019). Sex differences and trait intercorrelations in the dark triad of personality: A systematic review and psychometric meta-analysis [Unpublished master‘s thesis], University of Vienna.
dokumentation.researchQuestion: Univariate and multivariate sex differences in subclinical components of the Dark Triad of personality
dokumentation.literatureSelection: Inclusion: (1) Studies need to investigate the three components of the Dark Triad (narcissism, Machiavellianism, psychopathy) within one sample and (2) report results (mean and standard deviation) of men and women for the three traits
dokumentation.effectSize: Extraction of Hedges’ g for every study, either reported or calculated with reported outcomes (raw mean and standard deviation, t values, F values, or raw Pearson correlation between a Dark Triad trait and sex). Additionally, individual corrections for measurement error variances will be applied for Hedges’ g, following recommendations and formulas of Wiernik and Dahlke (2020) by using the R package ‘psychmeta’.
dokumentation.hierarchicalStructure: If a study reported several effect sizes for a sample, only one effect size was culled to ensure statistical independence of samples in the synthesis
